{
  "text": "The maximum net returns and net returns (Table  5) , per rupee invested (B:C ratio) were found with plant density of 80,000 ha -1 both lower and higher levels over 80,000 ha -1 reduced the net returns and benefit cost ratio. Sahoo and Maha (2007) and [CITATION_1] . The benefit cost ratio was also enhanced with higher nitrogen levels. Higher yields of green cobs and fodder directly contributed to the returns at higher nitrogen levels. Ashok (2009) observed similar results. The treatment combination of 80,000 plants ha -1 with application of 240 kg N ha -1 due to interaction gave maximum net returns and B:C ratio (4.25).",
